  "text": "It has also been reported that Tfcp2l1 is a repressor [CITATION_1] ). Consequently we analyzed genes that were upregulated in the knockouts and that demonstrated a Tfcp2l1-DNA interaction site ±50 KB from the gene's TSS. None of these genes were associated with a particular function or a cell-type in the distal nephron.",
